<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-11-03T19:44:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-11-03T19:44:00-05:00" n="334" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d334">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">882.5048/120: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Wharton</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Monrovia</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-11-04T00:00:00-00:44">November 4,
                                    1929—midnight</date>.<lb/>[Received November 5—8:21
                                p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>59. President’s message to the Liberian Legislature October 30, 2 p.m.,
                            considers in general terms slave trade question and quotes selected
                            extracts of first notes exchanged between the Government of Liberia and
                            this Legation. President promises copy which will be mailed.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Wharton</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>